This paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category as it focuses on improving interactivity in data analysis through visualization and interaction with intermediate results. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories as it discusses dimensionality reduction techniques such as t-SNE. Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) are also possible sub-categories as the paper deals with visualizing and analyzing high-dimensional data.
